Halve the @bell pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1} and remove the core and seeds. Chop into
small pieces. Trim the @spring onion{2} then slice thinly.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the peppers and half
the spring onion and stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @king prawns{120%g} and stir-fry for another ~{2%minutes}.

Squeeze the pouch of @steamed basmati rice{1} and open the packet then tip the rice into
your frying pan of veggies and prawns. Stir-fry for another ~{2-3%minutes} until the
rice is piping hot and the prawns are cooked.

> TIP: Adjust the heat if necessary to prevent the rice from catching.
> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the centre.

Stir the @sesame oil{24%ml} into the stir-fry. Season to taste with @salt{} and @?black
pepper{} if needed.

Serve the prawn fried rice in bowls finished with a drizzle of @soy sauce{25%ml} and a
sprinkle of the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!